{"questionId":"22229740","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>If the tree continues to follow this pattern of growth, its height will never exceed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> metres.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the smallest possible value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use infinite geometric series to find the total growth of the tree&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>S</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>37</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>62</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22229740","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.5c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the smallest possible value of k.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.11—Sum of infinite geometric sequences"],"memberSectionIds":[],"secti